seed_chunks:
In the outer lanes, power wears a clean badge and a dirty glove. **HelixKline Interstellar** sells “hazard mitigation” and salvage arbitration, underwriting rescue beacons while quietly buying wrecks that should never be found. Opposing them, the **Colonial Security Directorate** claims to protect shipping with lawful inspections, but runs erased black-site raids and hunts loose evidence like Mara. Between them drift the **Gutterlight Salvagers’ Union**, a ragged mutual-aid network that “keeps crews alive” with contracts and safe docks—yet traffics in forbidden flight recorders and maps of dead ships. HelixKline funds Directorate tasking; the Directorate squeezes the Union; the Union leaks corporate secrets to hurt both—until something in the derelicts starts using all three.

```json
{
  "factions": [
    {
      "name": "HelixKline Interstellar",
      "public_front": "Corporate hazard mitigation, salvage arbitration, and rescue underwriting.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Acquire and quarantine anomalous wrecks while erasing logs, witnesses, and competing claims."
    },
    {
      "name": "Colonial Security Directorate",
      "public_front": "Lawful shipping protection through inspections, patrols, and anti-piracy actions.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Operate black-site boarding actions and suppress any proof of nonhuman contact or prior failures."
    },
    {
      "name": "Gutterlight Salvagers’ Union",
      "public_front": "Mutual-aid collective providing crews with contracts, safe docks, and emergency support.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Smuggle restricted tech and flight recorders, selling truths to the highest bidder to break corporate control."
    }
  ]
}
```

HelixKline has quietly reactivated a “rescue” beacon on the derelict **Sable Hymn**, drawing scav crews like moths while a Directorate cutter, **CSD Valiant**, claims quarantine authority and begins stop-and-search seizures. The Gutterlight Union’s broker **Juno Rake** races to extract a sealed flight recorder before either side locks the hulk down—offering Mara a cut and a falsified transponder. Meanwhile, survivors from nearby wrecks report the same three-tap signal in their walls; power flickers in rhythmic bursts, and anyone who answers on open comms goes missing within the hour.

```json
{
  "events": [
    {
      "name": "The Sable Hymn Beacon Trap",
      "description": "HelixKline reactivates a 'distress' beacon on the derelict Sable Hymn to lure salvage crews, then moves to claim and quarantine the wreck under arbitration.",
      "tensions": [
        "Salvagers risk being baited into an anomalous kill-zone",
        "HelixKline legal teams and contracted security move to seize any recovered data",
        "False beacon pings create a time pressure window before lockdown"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "CSD Quarantine Sweep: Operation Clean Ledger",
      "description": "The Colonial Security Directorate cutter CSD Valiant declares quarantine jurisdiction and begins aggressive inspections, confiscating flight recorders and detaining crews with erased paperwork.",
      "tensions": [
        "Mara is at high risk of recognition and disappearance if boarded",
        "Union safe-docks are raided, forcing crews into unsafe routes",
        "Any recorded anomaly evidence becomes a trigger for lethal suppression"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "The Three-Tap Contagion",
      "description": "A repeating three-impact signal propagates through derelict comms and ship structures; those who respond on open channels vanish, and multiple wrecks experience synchronized power flickers.",
      "tensions": [
        "Crew paranoia spikes as the sound appears to 'listen back'",
        "Factions blame each other, escalating armed encounters in tight corridors",
        "The presence seems to be triangulating responders—turning comms into a weapon"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

